f=Brand Studio/rio/marketplace/sales-retargeting/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "sales-retargeting" (sales-skills/sales, 64★), fulfilling catalog's retargeting-playbooks slot ("audience segmentation sequential messaging patterns; frequency caps"). Chosen honesty: Gotchas section carries exactly caveats system enforces elsewhere view-through ROAS inflation, retargeting cannibalizing organic (true lift 40–60% reported), iOS/cookie erosion plus self-improving learnings.md convention matches our self-annealing rule. NOTES SYSTEM: source's /sales-{platform} skill ecosystem cross-skill fetch protocol source-repo machinery read sections pointers; platform-specific setup routes rio's ad-platform playbooks configured connectors. Email-retargeting strategy overlaps lena's email-marketer: strategy said here, sequence design sending discipline lena's. Budget-allocation suggestions (40/30/20) source's starting shapes actual allocations live rio-config board's budget envelope. --> · h1:Retargeting & Remarketing Strategy=Help user plan execute retargeting campaigns website visitor retargeting, cart abandonment recovery, dynamic product ads, cross-channel remarketing, audience segmentation. skill tool-agnostic includes platform-specific guidance. · h2:Step Gather context=`references/learnings.md` exists, read first accumulated knowledge. Ask user: **What's your retargeting goal?** · h2:Step Gather context=Recover abandoned carts (ecommerce), Re-engage website visitors who didn't convert, C) Upsell/cross-sell existing customers, Bring back lapsed users churned customers, Build full retargeting funnel scratch, sure help figure out what retarget · h2:Step Gather context=**What channels you want retarget on?** · h2:Step Gather context=Display ads (banner ads across web), Social ads (Facebook/Instagram, TikTok, LinkedIn), Google Ads (search remarketing, display network), Email retargeting (triggered website behavior), Connected (CTV) video, Multiple channels, sure recommend channels · h2:Step Gather context=**What retargeting platform you (or considering)?** · h2:Step Gather context=A) AdRoll, B) Google Ads (remarketing), Meta Ads (Facebook/Instagram retargeting), D) Criteo, LinkedIn Ads (website retargeting), Native ESP retargeting (Klaviyo, Omnisend, etc.), Remerge, Adwake, Zoomd (mobile in-app retargeting), None evaluating options, describe · h2:Step Gather context=**What's your business type?** · h2:Step Gather context=A) Ecommerce / D2C, B2B SaaS services, Local business services, D) Publisher / content, E) Other · h3:How retargeting works=Retargeting serves ads people who already interacted your brand visited your website, viewed products, added cart, engaged content. works through: **Pixel-based retargeting**: JavaScript pixel your site drops cookie (or uses first-party data) visitor. platforms use data serve ads visitors elsewhere web. **List-based retargeting**: Upload email lists CRM contacts platforms. platform matches against their user base serves ads matched users. **Server-side tracking**: Send conversion behavior events your server platforms directly reliable client-side pixels blockers. · h2:Step Retargeting reference=**Read `references/platform-guide.md`** detailed funnel frameworks, audience segmentation, frequency capping, creative strategy, platform-specific guidance, budget allocation. *You longer need platform guide details focus user's specific situation.* · h3:Quick-start: First retargeting campaign=**Install tracking** pixel your website server-side tracking available **Wait data** let 1-2 weeks visitor data accumulate (aim 1,000+ unique visitors your retargeting pool) **Segment audiences** create least segments: cart abandoners, product viewers, visitors **Create ads** 3-5 creative variants segment. Dynamic product ads cart/product viewers, brand ads general visitors. **Set budget** allocate 40-50% cart abandoners, 30% product viewers, 20% general visitors **Launch monitor** check daily first week. Watch ROAS, frequency, conversion rate segment. **Optimize** after 7-14 days, cut underperforming segments, increase budget high-ROAS segments, refresh creative. · h2:Gotchas=**Retargeting without fresh creative fatigue** mistake. Rotate creative 2-3 weeks. frequency high CTR declining, your audience tuned out your ads. **Don't retarget everyone way** cart abandoner $500 their cart needs different message someone who bounced your homepage seconds. Segment behavior value. **iOS tracking limitations** Apple's ATT framework (iOS 14.5+) significantly reduced pixel-based tracking accuracy Safari/iOS users. Use server-side tracking (Meta CAPI, Google Enhanced Conversions, AdRoll S2S) fill gap. **View-through attribution inflates ROAS** platforms count conversions happen after someone *saw* your ad, even they didn't click. View-through real weaker click-through. Compare click-through-only ROAS conservative measure. **Retargeting cannibalizes organic conversions** retargeted users converted anyway. Run incrementality tests (holdout groups) measure true lift. Typical true lift 40-60% reported retargeting conversions. **Cookie deprecation** third-party cookies phased out. Shift toward first-party data (email lists, logged-in users, server-side tracking) contextual targeting. Platforms strong first-party identity graphs (Meta, Google) maintain better targeting. · h2:Gotchas=**Self-improving**: you discover something covered here, append `references/learnings.md` today's date. · h2:Before recommending specific platform skill=skill covers strategy domain across many platforms. **Before pointing user any specific platform skill** (any `/sales-{platform}` listed `## Related skills`, e.g., `/sales-mailshake`, `/sales-klaviyo`, `/sales-apollo`), read platform skill's actual `SKILL.md` first. 1-line description `## Related skills` enough *identify* candidate it's enough *commit* write prompt invokes well. **How read it:** · h2:Before recommending specific platform skill=`~/.claude/skills/{skill-name}/SKILL.md` exists locally, `Read` it., `sales-*` skills, `WebFetch` directly repo: `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sales-skills/sales/main/skills/{skill-name}/SKILL.md` e.g., `sales-mailshake`: `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sales-skills/sales/main/skills/sales-mailshake/SKILL.md`., non-`sales-*` skills (third-party), look `{org}/{repo}` `~/.claude/skills/sales-do/references/skill-sources.md` installed fetch `skills/{skill-name}/SKILL.md` path under repo. · h2:Before recommending specific platform skill=**After reading,** ground your recommendation something concrete SKILL.md (its scope, sub-flow, `argument-hint` shape, "Do use for..." negative trigger). Align any generated invocation platform skill's `argument-hint`. platform skill turns out fit user's situation, swap another handle question directly rather recommending poor fit. · h2:Related skills=`/sales-retention` Retention.com platform help (ecommerce identity resolution, abandonment recovery), `/sales-customersai` Customers.ai platform help (ad retargeting audience recovery X-Ray identity resolution Meta, Google, TikTok), `/sales-adroll` AdRoll platform help (retargeting pixel, campaigns, audiences, RollWorks ABM, NextRoll API), `/sales-b2b-advertising` Account-based B2B advertising (ABM ads, consumer retargeting), `/sales-email-marketing` Email marketing strategy (email retargeting flows covered strategy, platform skills setup), `/sales-checkout` Checkout optimization (reducing abandonment source), `/sales-funnel` Funnel strategy (retargeting supports mid/bottom-funnel conversion), `/sales-audience-growth` Growing your email/subscriber list (retargeting list-growth tactic), `/sales-klaviyo` Klaviyo platform help (email/SMS retargeting flows ecommerce), `/sales-omnisend` Omnisend platform help (email/SMS retargeting ecommerce), `/sales-blueconic` BlueConic CDP build retargeting audiences unified profiles, activate segments platforms, `/sales-reddit-ads` Reddit Ads platform help (subreddit targeting, website retargeting, engagement audiences), `/sales-cloutboost` Cloutboost platform help gaming influencer retargeting, Portal discovery, campaign management, `/sales-gaming-marketing` Gaming influencer marketing strategy streamer partnerships, game launch campaigns, `/sales-remerge` Remerge platform help in-app retargeting DSP, audience segmentation, incrementality measurement, MMP integrations, `/sales-adwake` Adwake platform help managed mobile app UA, branding, in-app retargeting (Entravision), `/sales-zoomd` Zoomd platform help mobile across 600+ sources, mobile DSP, CGC, Albert.ai optimization, `/sales-do` sure which skill use? router matches any sales objective right skill. Install: `npx skills add sales-skills/sales --skill sales-do` · h3:Example Ecommerce cart recovery=**User says**: "We're losing 70% carts. set retargeting recover them?" **Skill does**: Designs multi-channel cart recovery strategy: email sequence (1hr, 24hr, 72hr), display retargeting dynamic product ads (AdRoll Google), social retargeting carousel ads (Meta). Provides timing, messaging, budget allocation. Recommends starting email (free) layering paid channels. **Result**: User complete cart recovery playbook across email paid retargeting. · h3:Example B2B website visitor retargeting=**User says**: "We get 10,000 monthly visitors our SaaS site convert. retarget rest?" **Skill does**: Recommends LinkedIn retargeting (professional audience), Google RLSA (capture search intent past visitors), display retargeting. Segments page: pricing page viewers get demo CTA ads, blog readers get lead magnet ads, homepage bouncers get brand awareness. Budgets accordingly. **Result**: User segmented B2B retargeting strategy channel budget recommendations. · h3:Example Choosing retargeting platform=**User says**: "I'm choosing between AdRoll, Criteo, using Google/Meta directly retargeting. What pick?" **Skill does**: Compares platforms use case: Google/Meta direct teams already advertising (simpler, extra vendor), AdRoll cross-channel retargeting one platform (good ecommerce, supports Shopify), Criteo large-scale ecommerce budget premium dynamic creative. Recommends based user's budget, business type, existing stack. **Result**: User platform recommendation clear trade-offs. · h3:Retargeting audiences small=**Symptom**: Platform says audience below minimum threshold (e.g., <100 users) **Cause**: Low website traffic, pixel installed pages, audience window narrow **Solution**: Extend lookback window days days days). Ensure pixel pages. Combine segments (product viewers cart abandoners). B2B low traffic, use list-based retargeting (email uploads) instead pixel-based. · h3:High frequency low conversions=**Symptom**: Users see your ads 10+ times aren't converting **Cause**: Creative fatigue, wrong audience segment, user isn't going buy regardless **Solution**: Cap frequency 3-5/day. Rotate creative. Move high-frequency non-converters "suppress" list after days. Consider visitors never qualified narrow your retargeting segments higher-intent behaviors. · h3:ROAS declining over time=**Symptom**: Retargeting ROAS strong initially dropped **Cause**: You've converted easy wins retargeting lower-intent users, creative gone stale **Solution**: Refresh creative. Narrow audiences higher-intent segments. Test new channels (add email using display, vice versa). Run incrementality test check true lift you need accept lower accurate ROAS figure.